Prior art acknowledgements
--------------------------

The CycloneDX -> OpenVEX vocabulary crosswalk in this library
(crosswalk/crosswalk.yaml) is seeded from the community mapping discussed in:

  * CycloneDX/specification Discussion #609
    "Mapping CycloneDX bi-directionally to Minimum Requirements for VEX"
    https://github.com/CycloneDX/specification/discussions/609

and anchored on the status/justification labels defined by:

  * CISA, "Minimum Requirements for Vulnerability Exploitability eXchange (VEX)"
    (April 2023). OpenVEX implements these labels verbatim.
    https://www.cisa.gov/resources-tools/resources/minimum-requirements-vulnerability-exploitability-exchange-vex

cyclonedx-to-openvex is not derived from those documents; they were read as
prior art to ground the mapping. The crosswalk records fidelity (exact / lossy
/ contested) for every entry so consumers can decide how much loss to accept.
